    "faq": {
      "type": "neycher-pdp-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What causes vaginal dryness?",
            "answer": "<p>Vaginal dryness is typically caused by an imbalance of hormones, which is most commonly associated with menopause. During menopause, estrogen levels decline, leading to thinner, drier vaginal tissue. Other causes include breastfeeding, certain medications, stress, and autoimmune conditions. If you're experiencing persistent dryness, it's always a good idea to consult with your healthcare provider.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What types of issues does the Ultra Moisturizing Complex help with?",
            "answer": "<p>The Ultra Moisturizing Complex helps with vaginal dryness, discomfort during intimacy, irritation, and general vaginal discomfort. It works by restoring moisture to vaginal tissue using hyaluronic acid and other hydrating ingredients that support long-lasting relief.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the Ultra Moisturizing Complex work?",
            "answer": "<p>Our suppositories use a combination of hyaluronic acid, vitamin A, vitamin E, and natural plant extracts to deeply hydrate vaginal tissue, restore pH balance, and support the healing of irritated or thinning tissue. The suppository format ensures direct, targeted delivery of active ingredients.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is hyaluronic acid safe for internal use?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Hyaluronic acid is a naturally occurring substance in your body and is widely used in medical and cosmetic applications. Our formulation uses pharmaceutical-grade hyaluronic acid sodium salt that is specifically designed for vaginal use and has been clinically tested for safety.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why suppositories?",
            "answer": "<p>Suppositories provide direct, targeted delivery of active ingredients to vaginal tissue. Unlike oral supplements that must pass through the digestive system, suppositories deliver hydration and healing compounds exactly where they're needed, resulting in faster and more effective relief.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long before I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>Many women notice improvement within the first few uses. For optimal results, we recommend using the suppositories consistently for 7-14 days. Long-term use can provide sustained moisture and comfort.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does the Ultra Moisturizing Complex have any side effects?",
            "answer": "<p>In our clinical trials, 96% of participants reported no side effects. Our formula is free from hormones, parabens, and harsh chemicals. If you experience any unusual irritation, discontinue use and consult your healthcare provider.</p>"
          }
        }
